<% include ../includes/header %>

	<div class="osu-layout__section osu-layout__section--full js-content community_forum-forums-index">
		<div id="forum-index-header" class="osu-layout__row osu-layout__row--page">
			<div class="text-area">
				<div class="text">
					<h2>welcome</h2>
					<h1>pls enjoy tournament 2017</h1>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="osu-layout__row">
			<% for (let type in messages) { %>
				<div class="alert alert-<%- type %>">
					<%- messages[type] %>
				</div>
				<% } %>
					<div id="forum-1" class="forum-category col-sm-12 forum-colour category-osu">
						<div class="row forum-category-header forum-colour__bg--category-osu">
							<div class="forum-category-header__name">General Information</div>
							<div class="forum-category-header__description">Welcome!</div>
						</div>
						<div class="forums osu-layout__sub-row">
							<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-12">
									<p>Welcome to <b>pls enjoy tournament</b>! This is the official site for the tournament. Please check this site regularly
										during the competition, as updates, mappool, and rankings will all be posted here. Registration for this tournament
										will take place on this site, rather than through the forum. The registration form will open on <b>May 20</b>.</p>
									<div class="page-header">
										<h4>Dates</h4>
									</div>
									<ul>
										<li>Registrations: <b>May 20 - June 17</b></li>
										<li>Drawings: <b>June 18 - June 19</b></li>
										<li>Group Stages: <b>June 24 - June 30</b></li>
										<li>Round of 16: <b>July 1 - July 2</b></li>
										<li>Quarterfinals: <b>July 8 - July 9</b></li>
										<li>Semifinals: <b>July 15 - July 16</b></li>
										<li>Finals: <b>July 22 - July 23</b></li>
										<li>Grand Finals: <b>July 29 - July 30</b></li>
									</ul>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div id="forum-2" class="forum-category col-sm-12 forum-colour category-beatmaps">
						<div class="row forum-category-header forum-colour__bg--category-beatmaps">
							<div class="forum-category-header__name">Format</div>
							<div class="forum-category-header__description">Logistics about the competition.</div>
						</div>
						<div class="forums osu-layout__sub-row">
							<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-12">
									<ul>
										<li>This is an <b>2v2 double-elimination</b> tournament.</li>
										<li>The minimum amount of players required per team is <b>3</b> and the maximum is <b>4</b>.</li>
										<li>There are a maximum of <b>32 teams</b> that can participate in the tournament.</li>
										<li>The tournament will comprise of a <b>group</b> stage and a <b>double elimination</b> round.</li>
										<li>In the double elimination round, Last Man Standing begins; the lowest scoring player of each map played will be
											knocked out.</li>
										<li>Game mode is <b>Team VS</b>, and played on <b>Score v2</b>.</li>
									</ul>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div id="forum-3" class="forum-category col-sm-12 forum-colour category-other">
						<div class="row forum-category-header forum-colour__bg--category-other">
							<div class="forum-category-header__name">Rules</div>
							<div class="forum-category-header__description">Rules of the game.</div>
						</div>
						<div class="forums osu-layout__sub-row">
							<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-12">
									<ul>
										<li>The rank limit upon entry will be <b>1,000</b> - <b>20,000</b>; going outside of the range during the tournament
											will result in disqualification.</li>
										<li>A player failing a map has the opportunity to revive and his/her score will not be invalidated. However, a team
											fail will count as a loss.</li>
										<li>If a team fails, then the player with the lowest score on the failing team will lose a life.</li>
										<li>Players are invited at least 15 minutes before their match start.</li>
										<li>If a team fails to yield a full roster of at least 2 players within 15 minutes of their scheduled match time, they
											will forfeit the match. There will not be an opportunity to reschedule matches forfeited in this manner.</li>
									</ul>
									<div class="page-header">
										<h4>Group Stage</h4>
									</div>
									<ul>
										<li>There will be no warm-up maps.</li>
										<li>Each team will be allowed two bans.</li>
										<li>The group stages are played in a round-robin format, with the top 2 teams in each group moving on.</li>
										<li>It will be Best of 5, 3 points will win the match.</li>
										<li>There will be 4 NM, 3 HD, HR, DT, FM and 1 TB.</li>
										<li>Group stages will take place over the course of 2 weeks.</li>
									</ul>
									<div class="page-header">
										<h4>Double Elimination</h4>
									</div>
									<ul>
										<li>At the end of each map, the player on <b>either side</b> with the LOWEST score will lose a life; this is the Last
											Man Standing concept - if a player is out of lives, they are considered out of the round, and their score will
											no longer be counted for the rest of the match (they can choose whether to stay in the MP room or not).</li>
										<li>The tiebreaker map will be played if both teams have a total of one life each, and <b>team score will matter regardless of lives (team with the highest collective score wins).</b></li>
									</ul>
									<div class="page-header">
										<h4>Quarterfinals</h4>
									</div>
									<ul>
										<li>Matches will be played in Last Man Standing format!</li>
										<li>From RO16 and onwards, there will be warmup maps and 2 bans.</li>
										<li>It will be Best of 7, 4 points will win the match.</li>
										<li>There will be 4 NM, 3 HD, HR, DT, FM and 3 TB.</li>
									</ul>
									<div class="page-header">
										<h4>Semifinals & Finals</h4>
									</div>
									<ul>
										<li>Matches will be played in Last Man Standing format!</li>
										<li>It will be Best of 11, 6 points will win the match.</li>
										<li>There will be 4 NM, 4 HD, HR, DT, FM and 3 TB.</li>
										<li>Each round will last 1 week.</li>
									</ul>
									<div class="page-header">
										<h4>Grand Finals</h4>
									</div>
									<ul>
										<li>Matches will be played in Last Man Standing format!</li>
										<li>It will be Best of 13, 7 points will win the match.</li>
										<li>There will be 5 NM, 4 HD, HR, DT, FM and 3 TB.</li>
										<li>There will be a bracket reset if necessary.</li>
									</ul>
									<div class="page-header">
										<h4>The Match</h4>
									</div>
									<ul>
										<li>One member of each team will !roll, and the one with the higher number can choose either to ban first or second.</li>
										<li>Each team alternates banning maps until there are a total of 4 banned maps (each team has a total of <b>2</b> banned
											maps).</li>
										<li>Tiebreaker cannot be banned.</li>
										<li>The higher rolling team gets to pick the first warm-up map <b>and</b> the first actual map.</li>
										<li>Warm-up maps must be less than <b>5:30</b></li>
									</ul>
									<h5>Substitutions</h5>
									<ul>
										<li>If a team wishes to substitute a player, the substitute does not get a new stock of full lives but receives the
											number of lives held by the player subbed out for the substitute.</li>
										<li>There is to be only one substitution per map.</li>
										<li>Two active players can not substitute for one another.</li>
									</ul>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div id="forum-2" class="forum-category col-sm-12 forum-colour category-language-specific">
						<div class="row forum-category-header forum-colour__bg--category-language-specific">
							<div class="forum-category-header__name">Map Pool</div>
